  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0daf\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It is reasonable to set fire to stolen houses",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Chaminda Wijesiri, member of Samagi Jana Balawega, Badulla district, said in Parliament that it is reasonable to burn the houses built by stealing money.",
        "Mr. Wijesiri, who said that theft has not disappeared, said that all 225 are being branded because they are protecting those who have stolen and if there has been theft, there is no problem in burning down Chaminda's house.",
        "The Minister of Urban Development and Housing Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga said that if it is fair to say that it is fair to burn the houses of those who stole, not even a single person will be allowed to live there."
      ],
